    "method": [
        {
            "text": "Skin the tomatoes, separate the flesh, and reserve the seeds. Heat 2 tablespoons of Oil in a saucepan and add the Tomatoes along with the juice from the Seeds, a good bit of Salt and a pinch of Chilli Flakes. Mash them a bit, and leave to bubble for 30 minutes or so until they get to a sauce consistency",
            "post_notes": [],
            "pre_notes": [],
            "type": "METHOD_STEP"
        },
        {
            "text": "Next, make the basil and garlic oil. Add the Oil, Garlic, Basil, and Chilli Flakes to a pan and heat very slowly until the Garlic is very slightly browned (around 20 minutes)",
            "post_notes": [],
            "pre_notes": [],
            "type": "METHOD_STEP"
        },
        {
            "text": "Strain the Oil and stir into the Tomato Sauce. Season with Salt",
            "post_notes": [],
            "pre_notes": [],
            "type": "METHOD_STEP"
        },
        {
            "text": "To Complete",
            "post_notes": [],
            "pre_notes": [],
            "type": "METHOD_STEP"
        },
        {
            "text": "Cook Spaghetti until almost done. Reserve some of the pasta water and drain. Add enough Tomato Sauce to a pan, add in the Spaghetti and some of the reserved pasta water. Cook until the sauce has a good consistency, then add the chopped basil, Parmesan, and Butter. Mix well and serve",
